3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network settles funding payments hourly across its shared order book infrastructure, which aggregates liquidity from multiple frontend partners. The funding rate calculation follows standard perpetual swap mechanics, but benefits from deeper liquidity pools due to the unified order book serving various DEX frontends. Cross-chain settlement capabilities allow for more complex arbitrage strategies between NEAR and EVM-compatible chains."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TIA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA represents infrastructure layer value in the modular blockchain ecosystem, creating predictable funding rate cycles around network upgrades and validator set changes. The token's utility in securing Celestia's data availability layer generates consistent demand patterns that sophisticated traders can exploit through funding rate arbitrage."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA funding rates on Orderly Network typically range from -0.01% to 0.05% hourly, with notable spikes during Celestia network upgrades and rollup adoption phases. Infrastructure tokens like TIA show less volatility in funding rates compared to meme coins but more predictable cycles tied to validator economics. The shared liquidity model provides more stable rate discovery compared to isolated DEX perpetuals. Historical data shows TIA funding rates correlate with overall modular blockchain narrative cycles and DA layer utilization metrics."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Chain Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly's multi-chain infrastructure creates unique arbitrage opportunities between NEAR and EVM-based TIA markets. Traders can exploit funding rate differentials between Orderly's shared book and centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX. The 1-hour settlement frequency allows for more granular position management compared to 8-hour cycles on traditional CEXs. Arbitrageurs should monitor gas costs across different chains when executing cross-platform strategies, as NEAR's low fees provide advantages over Ethereum-based competitors."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA's infrastructure token status creates specific risk factors including validator slashing events and network upgrade uncertainties that can cause rapid funding rate shifts. Orderly's dependence on frontend partners introduces counterparty risks not present in traditional CEXs. The shared order book model, while providing liquidity benefits, can create cascading liquidation risks during market stress. Traders should account for potential smart contract risks in the underlying infrastructure and maintain diversified exposure across multiple venues when executing funding rate strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Orderly Network settle TIA funding payments?","answer":"Orderly Network settles TIA funding payments every hour, providing more frequent cash flow opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles on most centralized exchanges. This creates additional arbitrage windows for active traders."},{"question":"What makes TIA funding rates unique on Orderly's shared liquidity model?","answer":"The shared order book aggregates TIA liquidity from multiple DEX frontends, creating deeper markets and more stable funding rate discovery. This infrastructure reduces the extreme rate spikes common on smaller DEX perpetual platforms."},{"question":"How do Celestia network events affect TIA funding rates?","answer":"Major Celestia upgrades, validator set changes, and DA layer adoption by new rollups typically drive temporary funding rate premiums as traders position for infrastructure demand. These events create predictable arbitrage opportunities for prepared traders."},{"question":"What are the key risks of TIA arbitrage on Orderly Network?","answer":"Primary risks include smart contract vulnerabilities in the shared infrastructure, dependency on frontend partner stability, and TIA-specific risks like validator slashing or network governance changes that can cause rapid price movements."}]}]
